FBIS3-8851 "dreeu052__a94020" FBIS-EEU-94-052-A Document Type:Daily Report 16 Mar 1994 ANNEX Slovakia CTK Profiles New Cabinet Members Privatization Minister Milan Janicina AU1603204894 Prague CTK in English 1947 GMT 16 Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1603204894 Prague CTK Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Prague, March 16 (CTK) -- Milan Janicina, lawyer by profession, was appointed new Slovak minister for the administration and privatisation of national property today, at the proposal of the so-called Center Bloc. Janicina was born on December 13, 1948, in Bratislava. In 1973 he graduated from the law faculty of Comenius University in Bratislava and then worked as a lawyer for Slovak Television and for other institutions. In 1990 he was an adviser to the government legislative department. Until March 1992 he was deputy head of the legal department in the Ministry for the Administration and Privatization of National Property. From May 1993 he was deputy chairman of the Slovak Office of Geodesy and Cartography. Janicina has been a parliament deputy for the Slovak National Party (SNS) since November 1993 and since December 1993 he has been a member of the SNS national democratic deputies' group of former SNS Chairman Ludovit Cernak.
